appAccelerationStatusMIB.name: appAccelerationStatusMIB
appAccelerationStatusMIB.contactinfo: Citrix Systems, Inc. Postal: 851 West Cypress Creek Road Fort Lauderdale, Florida 33309 United States
appAccelerationStatusMIB.description: This module defines the status variables that can be retrieved from a Citrix Application Acceleration unit.

wsOperStatus.name: wsOperStatus
wsOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the unit.

wsLoad1Min.name: wsLoad1Min
wsLoad1Min.description: The 1 minute load average that is also available in the Unix TOP or UPTIME commands. It reports the average number of processes ready to be run. The value is computed by taking the load average value and multiplying it by 100, then converting the value to an integer.

wsLoad5Min.name: wsLoad5Min
wsLoad5Min.description: The 5 minute load average that is also available in the Unix TOP or UPTIME commands. It reports the average number of processes ready to be run. The value is computed by taking the load average value and multiplying it by 100, then converting the value to an integer.

wsLoad15Min.name: wsLoad15Min
wsLoad15Min.description: The 15 minute load average that is also available in the Unix TOP or UPTIME commands. It reports the average number of processes ready to be run. The value is computed by taking the load average value and multiplying it by 100, then converting the value to an integer.

wsBypass.name: wsBypass
wsBypass.description: Traffic processing status. This is also available in the GUI Features page.

wsLastAlarmSeqNum.name: wsLastAlarmSeqNum
wsLastAlarmSeqNum.description: The value of the alarm sequence number for the last alarm generated as a trap.

wsBoostStatus.name: wsBoostStatus
wsBoostStatus.description: The selected boost mode. This is also available in the GUI Bandwidth Management page.

wsBandwidthMode.name: wsBandwidthMode
wsBandwidthMode.description: The selected bandwidth usage. This is also available in the GUI Bandwidth Management page.

wsBandwidthLimit.name: wsBandwidthLimit
wsBandwidthLimit.description: Send bandwidth limit. This is also available in the GUI Bandwidth Management page.

wsWanOutOctets.name: wsWanOutOctets
wsWanOutOctets.description: Number of accelerated octets transmitted on the WAN side. This is also available in the GUI Usage Graph page.

wsWanInOctets.name: wsWanInOctets
wsWanInOctets.description: Number of accelerated octets received on the WAN side. This is also available in the GUI Usage Graph page.

wsLanOutOctets.name: wsLanOutOctets
wsLanOutOctets.description: Number of accelerated octets transmitted on the LAN side. This is also available in the GUI Usage Graph page.

wsLanInOctets.name: wsLanInOctets
wsLanInOctets.description: Number of accelerated octets received on the LAN side. This is also available in the GUI Usage Graph page.

wsCompressionEffectiveBandwidth.name: wsCompressionEffectiveBandwidth
wsCompressionEffectiveBandwidth.description: The equivalent throughput before compression. This is also available in the GUI Compression Status page. This variable may be reset from the above web page.

wsSendCompressionRatio.name: wsSendCompressionRatio
wsSendCompressionRatio.description: Average send compression rate per 1000 octets, e.g. 3500 means 3.5 to 1 compression. This is also available in the GUI Compression Status page. This variable may be reset from the above web page.

wsReceiveCompressionRatio.name: wsReceiveCompressionRatio
wsReceiveCompressionRatio.description: Average receive compression rate per 1000 octets, e.g. 3500 means 3.5 to 1 compression. This is also available in the GUI Compression Status page. This variable may be reset from the above web page.

wsCompressionStatsCollectionTime.name: wsCompressionStatsCollectionTime
wsCompressionStatsCollectionTime.description: The number of centiseconds (0.01 seconds) since the start of the compression statistics collection. This is also available in the GUI Compression Status page. This variable may be reset from the above web page.

wsAcceleratedConnections.name: wsAcceleratedConnections
wsAcceleratedConnections.description: Number of current accelerated (active + inactive) connections. This is also available in the GUI System Status page.

wsNonAcceleratedConnections.name: wsNonAcceleratedConnections
wsNonAcceleratedConnections.description: Number of current non-accelerated connections. This is also available in the GUI System Status page.

wsHaState.name: wsHaState
wsHaState.description: High availability state of the unit. This is also available in the GUI High Availability page.

wsHaVmIp.name: wsHaVmIp
wsHaVmIp.description: Virtual Management IP Address used in HA setup. This is also available in the GUI High Availability page.

wsHaSecondaryIp.name: wsHaSecondaryIp
wsHaSecondaryIp.description: When retrieved from the primary unit (in HA configuration), this is the IP Address of the secondary unit. When retrieved from a secondary or standalone unit, this is 0.0.0.0. This is also available in the GUI High Availability page.

wsPrimaryIp.name: wsPrimaryIp
wsPrimaryIp.description: IP Address of the Primary Port, which is for management data.

wsCpuUsage.name: wsCpuUsage
wsCpuUsage.description: Averaged percent CPU used by the traffic accelerator in the last minute.

wsConnectedPlugIns.name: wsConnectedPlugIns
wsConnectedPlugIns.description: Current number of Plug-ins connected to this unit. This is also available in the GUI System Status page.

wsMaxPlugIns.name: wsMaxPlugIns
wsMaxPlugIns.description: The Maximum number of Plug-ins that are allowed to connect to this unit. This is also available in the GUI System Status page.

wsQosStatsCollectionTime.name: wsQosStatsCollectionTime
wsQosStatsCollectionTime.description: The number of centiseconds (0.01 seconds) since the start of the QoS and ICA statistics collection. This is also available in the GUI QoS Statistics page. This variable may be reset from the above web page.

wsUpTime.name: wsUpTime
wsUpTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the unit was last re-initialized.

wsNonAcceleratedVolume.name: wsNonAcceleratedVolume
wsNonAcceleratedVolume.description: Total non-accelerated k-bytes received by the unit, on all interfaces.

wsActiveConnections.name: wsActiveConnections
wsActiveConnections.description: Number of active accelerated connections. This is also available in the GUI System Status page.

wsAccelerationStatus.name: wsAccelerationStatus
wsAccelerationStatus.description: Traffic acceleration (flow control and compression) status. This is also available in the GUI Features page.

wsTrafficShapingStatus.name: wsTrafficShapingStatus
wsTrafficShapingStatus.description: Traffic shaping (QoS) status. This is also available in the GUI Features page.

wsWanSendRate.name: wsWanSendRate
wsWanSendRate.description: The average WAN side send rate in the last minute.

wsWanReceiveRate.name: wsWanReceiveRate
wsWanReceiveRate.description: The average WAN side receive rate in the last minute.

wsLanSendRate.name: wsLanSendRate
wsLanSendRate.description: The average LAN side send rate in the last minute.

wsLanReceiveRate.name: wsLanReceiveRate
wsLanReceiveRate.description: The average LAN side receive rate in the last minute.

wsNonAcceleratedRate.name: wsNonAcceleratedRate
wsNonAcceleratedRate.description: The average non-accelerated traffic rate in the last minute.

wsWccpStatus.name: wsWccpStatus
wsWccpStatus.description: WCCP status. This is also available in the GUI Features page.

wsActiveAlarmTable.name: wsActiveAlarmTable
wsActiveAlarmTable.description: A list of the active alarm entries. This represents the fault conditions that are still active in the unit.

activeAlarmEntry.name: activeAlarmEntry
activeAlarmEntry.description: The active alarm entries that are still valid system faults. RFC2578 (SMIv2) requires this to be not-accessible.

wsActiveAlarmIndex.name: wsActiveAlarmIndex
wsActiveAlarmIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the active alarm table.

wsActiveAlarmSeqNum.name: wsActiveAlarmSeqNum
wsActiveAlarmSeqNum.description: The active alarm's sequence number at the time it was generated.

wsActiveAlarmID.name: wsActiveAlarmID
wsActiveAlarmID.description: The OID identifying the actual trap that was generated.

wsActiveAlarmSeverity.name: wsActiveAlarmSeverity
wsActiveAlarmSeverity.description: The alarm severity for the active alarm.

wsActiveAlarmLogTime.name: wsActiveAlarmLogTime
wsActiveAlarmLogTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the alarm was generated.

wsActiveAlarmDesc.name: wsActiveAlarmDesc
wsActiveAlarmDesc.description: A description for the active alarm.

wsActiveAlarmAcked.name: wsActiveAlarmAcked
wsActiveAlarmAcked.description: Identifies if the user has acknowledged the alarm.

wsActiveAlarmServiceAffect.name: wsActiveAlarmServiceAffect
wsActiveAlarmServiceAffect.description: Identifies if the alarm is service affecting.

wsServiceClassStatsTable.name: wsServiceClassStatsTable
wsServiceClassStatsTable.description: A list of service class statistics entries. This contains the performance statistics separated by service classes.

wsServiceClassStatsEntry.name: wsServiceClassStatsEntry
wsServiceClassStatsEntry.description: Each service class entry contains the performance statistics for one service class.

wsServiceClassIndex.name: wsServiceClassIndex
wsServiceClassIndex.description: This is used as an index that uniquely identifies a service class in the service class statistics table.

wsServiceClassName.name: wsServiceClassName
wsServiceClassName.description: Name of the service class, e.g. HTTP, FTP, SMTP, CIFS, etc. The list of service classes monitored is defined in the GUI Configure Settings: Service Class page.

wsScsCurrentAcceleratedConnections.name: wsScsCurrentAcceleratedConnections
wsScsCurrentAcceleratedConnections.description: Current number of accelerated connections for the service class. This is also available in the GUI Service Class Statistics Detail page. This counter is reset only on system restart.

wsScsTotalAcceleratedConnections.name: wsScsTotalAcceleratedConnections
wsScsTotalAcceleratedConnections.description: Total number of accelerated connections for the service class. This is also available in the GUI Service Class Statistics Detail page. This counter is reset only on system restart.

wsScsTotalAcceleratedOctets.name: wsScsTotalAcceleratedOctets
wsScsTotalAcceleratedOctets.description: Total number of accelerated octets for the service class. This is also available in the GUI Service Class Statistics Detail page. This counter is reset only on system restart.

wsScsTotalNonAcceleratedConnections.name: wsScsTotalNonAcceleratedConnections
wsScsTotalNonAcceleratedConnections.description: Total number of non-accelerated connections for the service class. This is also available in the GUI Service Class Statistics Detail page. This counter is reset only on system restart.

wsScsTotalNonAcceleratedOctets.name: wsScsTotalNonAcceleratedOctets
wsScsTotalNonAcceleratedOctets.description: Total number of non-accelerated octets for the service class. This is also available in the GUI Service Class Statistics Detail page. This counter is reset only on system restart.

wsScsTotalPreCompressionOctets.name: wsScsTotalPreCompressionOctets
wsScsTotalPreCompressionOctets.description: Total number of accelerated octets for the service class before compression.

wsScsCompressSentOctets.name: wsScsCompressSentOctets
wsScsCompressSentOctets.description: Number of accelerated octets sent for the service class after compression.

wsScsCompressReceivedOctets.name: wsScsCompressReceivedOctets
wsScsCompressReceivedOctets.description: Number of accelerated octets received for the service class after compression.

wsScsPreCompressSentOctets.name: wsScsPreCompressSentOctets
wsScsPreCompressSentOctets.description: Number of accelerated octets sent for the service class before compression.

wsScsPreCompressReceivedOctets.name: wsScsPreCompressReceivedOctets
wsScsPreCompressReceivedOctets.description: Number of accelerated octets received for the service class before compression.

wsScsSendBWSavings.name: wsScsSendBWSavings
wsScsSendBWSavings.description: WAN-side send bandwidth savings. 100% meant very high (above 99.5:1) compression. 0% meant no compression savings. The formula is (Pre-compress-send-bytes - Compressed-send-bytes) / Pre-compress-send-bytes * 100%

wsScsRecvBWSavings.name: wsScsRecvBWSavings
wsScsRecvBWSavings.description: WAN-side receive bandwidth savings. 100% meant very high (above 99.5:1) compression. 0% meant no compression savings. The formula is (Pre-compress-received-bytes - Compressed-received-bytes) / Pre-compress-received-bytes * 100%

wsScsSendRecvBWSavings.name: wsScsSendRecvBWSavings
wsScsSendRecvBWSavings.description: Combined send and receive bandwidth savings. The formula is (Pre-compress-bytes - Compressed-bytes) / Pre-compress-bytes * 100%

wsScsSendCompressionRatio.name: wsScsSendCompressionRatio
wsScsSendCompressionRatio.description: WAN-side send compression ratio per 1000 octets, e.g. 3500 means 3.5 to 1 compression.

wsScsRecvCompressionRatio.name: wsScsRecvCompressionRatio
wsScsRecvCompressionRatio.description: WAN-side receive compression ratio per 1000 octets, e.g. 3500 means 3.5 to 1 compression.

wsScsSendRecvCompressionRatio.name: wsScsSendRecvCompressionRatio
wsScsSendRecvCompressionRatio.description: Combined send and receive compression ratio per 1000 octets, e.g. 3500 means 3.5 to 1 compression.

wsQosTrafficClassStatsTable.name: wsQosTrafficClassStatsTable
wsQosTrafficClassStatsTable.description: A list of QoS traffic class statistics.

wsQosTcStatsEntry.name: wsQosTcStatsEntry
wsQosTcStatsEntry.description: Each entry contains performance statistics for one QoS traffic class.

wsQosIndex.name: wsQosIndex
wsQosIndex.description: This index uniquely identifies a QoS traffic class in the QoS traffic class statistics table.

wsQosName.name: wsQosName
wsQosName.description: Name of the QoS traffic class, which is defined in the GUI Configure Settings: QoS page.

wsQosConfiguredSendRatio.name: wsQosConfiguredSendRatio
wsQosConfiguredSendRatio.description: The minimum share of the bandwidth configured for this traffic class. This is also available in the GUI QoS Statistics page.

wsQosSentVolume.name: wsQosSentVolume
wsQosSentVolume.description: The total volume of QoS traffic sent for this queue, measured in 1000-octets. This counter may be reset from the GUI QoS Statistics page. The wsQosStatsCollectionTime variable indicates when the counter was reset.

wsQosActualSendRatio.name: wsQosActualSendRatio
wsQosActualSendRatio.description: The bandwidth used by this traffic class. This is calculated using the wsQosSentVolume for the traffic class divided by the sum of wsQosSentVolume of all traffic classes.

wsIcaStatsTable.name: wsIcaStatsTable
wsIcaStatsTable.description: A list of ICA Traffic Presentation Layer statistics.

wsIcaStatsEntry.name: wsIcaStatsEntry
wsIcaStatsEntry.description: Each entry contains the performance statistics for one ICA priority.

wsIcaIndex.name: wsIcaIndex
wsIcaIndex.description: This is used as an index that uniquely identifies an ICA service in the ICA Traffic Presentation Layer statistics table.

wsIcaServiceName.name: wsIcaServiceName
wsIcaServiceName.description: Name of the ICA service, which is also in the GUI QoS Statistics page, Citrix ICA Traffic Presentation Layer Statistics section.

wsIcaPriority.name: wsIcaPriority
wsIcaPriority.description: The ICA Priorities: high is for realtime traffic, medium is for interactive traffic, low is for bulk transfer traffic, background is for the lowest priority traffic. This is no longer applicable starting from release 6.0.

wsIcaSentVolume.name: wsIcaSentVolume
wsIcaSentVolume.description: The total volume of traffic sent for this ICA applications measured in 1000-octets. This counter may be reset from the GUI QoS Statistics page.

wsIcaSentRatio.name: wsIcaSentRatio
wsIcaSentRatio.description: The sent volume as a percent share of the different ICA applications.

wsIcaReceivedVolume.name: wsIcaReceivedVolume
wsIcaReceivedVolume.description: The total volume of traffic received for this ICA application, measured in 1000-octets. This counter may be reset from the GUI QoS Statistics page.

wsIcaReceivedRatio.name: wsIcaReceivedRatio
wsIcaReceivedRatio.description: The received volume as a percent share of the different priority of the service. This counter may be reset from the GUI QoS Statistics page.

wsIcaSendRate.name: wsIcaSendRate
wsIcaSendRate.description: The last minute send rate of this ICA application.

wsIcaReceiveRate.name: wsIcaReceiveRate
wsIcaReceiveRate.description: The last minute receive rate of this ICA application.

wsAdapterTable.name: wsAdapterTable
wsAdapterTable.description: A list of adapters configured for the unit. It is also in the GUI IP Address page.

wsAdapterEntry.name: wsAdapterEntry
wsAdapterEntry.description: Each entry contains performance statistics for one ADAPTER.

wsAdapterIndex.name: wsAdapterIndex
wsAdapterIndex.description: This is used as an index that uniquely identifies an adapter.

linkStatsEntry.name: linkStatsEntry
linkStatsEntry.description: Each entry contains the performance statistics for one link.

linkIndex.name: linkIndex
linkIndex.description: This index uniquely identifies a link in the link statistics table.

linkSentVolume.name: linkSentVolume
linkSentVolume.description: The total volume of traffic sent on the link, measured in 1000-octets.

linkReceivedVolume.name: linkReceivedVolume
linkReceivedVolume.description: The total volume of traffic received on the link, measured in 1000-octets.

linkSentPackets.name: linkSentPackets
linkSentPackets.description: The total number of packets sent on the link.

linkReceivedPackets.name: linkReceivedPackets
linkReceivedPackets.description: The total number of packets received on the link. in 1000-octets.

linkDroppedSentVolume.name: linkDroppedSentVolume

linkDroppedReceivedVolume.name: linkDroppedReceivedVolume

linkDroppedSentPackets.name: linkDroppedSentPackets
linkDroppedSentPackets.description: The total number of packets not sent on the link due to QoS threshold.

linkDroppedReceivedPackets.name: linkDroppedReceivedPackets
linkDroppedReceivedPackets.description: The total number of received packets dropped from the link due to QoS threshold.

appStatsEntry.name: appStatsEntry
appStatsEntry.description: Each entry contains the performance statistics for one application on one link.

appIndex.name: appIndex
appIndex.description: This index uniquely identifies one application on a link.

appGroupId.name: appGroupId
appGroupId.description: Bit mask, indicating the group which this application belong to.

appSentVolume.name: appSentVolume
appSentVolume.description: The total volume of traffic sent on the link, measured in 1000-octets.

appReceivedVolume.name: appReceivedVolume
appReceivedVolume.description: The total volume of traffic sent on the link, measured in 1000-octets.

appSentPackets.name: appSentPackets
appSentPackets.description: The total volume of traffic sent on the link, measured in 1000-octets.

appReceivedPackets.name: appReceivedPackets
appReceivedPackets.description: The total volume of traffic sent on the link, in 1000-octets.

appDroppedSentVolume.name: appDroppedSentVolume
appDroppedSentVolume.description: The total traffic not sent on the link due to QoS threshold, in 1000-octets.

appDroppedReceiveVolume.name: appDroppedReceiveVolume
appDroppedReceiveVolume.description: The total received traffic dropped from the link due to QoS threshold, in 1000-octets.

appDroppedSentPackets.name: appDroppedSentPackets
appDroppedSentPackets.description: The total number of packets not sent on the link due to QoS threshold.

appDroppedReceivedPackets.name: appDroppedReceivedPackets
appDroppedReceivedPackets.description: The total number of received packets dropped from the link due to QoS threshold.

appSendRate.name: appSendRate
appSendRate.description: The last minute send rate of this application.

appReceiveRate.name: appReceiveRate
appReceiveRate.description: The last minute receive rate of this application.
